<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="273" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,259,717]" pageId="23" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,619,645]" pageId="23" pageNumber="273">Remarks.</emphasis>
Mountainous-xerophyte plant communities are typical of arid regions of Transcaucasia and the Mediterranean. Thus, the occurence of this species in similar biotopes North of the Great Caucasus Mtn. Range is quite natural.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
